  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (inadequate metrics variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is reported via aggregate goodness-of-fit metrics (R² and RMSE across all operating points) that appear rigorous but do not directly address the COU's actual question of interest: identification of worst-case hemolysis conditions. The metrics summarise average model fidelity rather than worst-case prediction accuracy, constituting an inadequate-metrics gap.",
