      "description": "CFD-predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against experimental measurements at all five flow-speed operating points. The aggregate coefficient of determination R² = 0.94 and root-mean-square error RMSE = 0.0031 mg/100 L indicate strong overall model fidelity. These statistics were computed across the full operating envelope, providing a compact summary of predictive accuracy. The high R² value supports the conclusion that the CFD model reliably reproduces experimental hemolysis trends and is therefore suitable for use in the CPB credibility assessment. Validation is considered passed at the required level.",
